dc_title_s: Sketch map showing the mineral & silk districts of the Province of Shan-tung (China) to accompany the paper by J. Markham Esqre., H. M. Consul at Chefoo
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures. Depth shown by soundings. Distribution of gold, cotton, galena, pongee silk, marble, lead, copper, iron, mulberry tree, asbestos, white copper, precious stone, and coal resources is shown. Mr. Markham's route shown in red. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 40, (1870), pp. 207-28; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.40 1870
dc_publisher_s: London: published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1870.
